Program: The Documentary
Title: Universality
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03sxn01
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 15 May 2016
Human rights may aspire to be universal - they should belong to everyone, everywhere - but there has been resistance to them on philosophical or theological grounds by powerful states and world religions. Lawyer Helena Kennedy looks at these issues and the rise of the human rights movement since 1948. (Photo: Algerian women hold a flag on which is written the Universal Declaration of Human Rights. Credit: AFP/Getty Images) Show less